e an issue—though avoiding it seems best. Yet, the native must run. I'll need to check if the agent captures test classes properly and figure out if static references by annotation impact this. I should keep one-to-one mapping and create a new file named WsServerContainerTest.java while maintaining the existing placeholder.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Exploring context implementation**\\n\\nI’m considering whether I need imports without qualified names and if I could implement a fake context inner class instead. I'm wondering if using `org.apache.catalina.core.StandardContext` makes sense since it's part of tomcat-embed-core. However, StandardContext is a container context, not a ServletContext, so I'd need to use getServletContext. I might instantiate it, but I'm unsure if it's started. I'll need to focus on how `WsSci.onStartup` calls for `ctx.addListener`, while ensuring our fake addListener does nothing. I'll also need to verify mappings and constructor flags related to the Configurator and Encoder.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating Java implementation details**\\n\\nI need to check if the set includes the endpoint; if it does, I’ll add the endpoint class to scannedPojoEndpoints. There might be a potential issue if `jreCompat.isExported(clazz)` returns false for unnamed modules, which I think is true. I should consider the Java version—maybe starting with source 8, since Tomcat 9 uses Java 8. I want to avoid using List.of and stick with Collections.singleton. Also, should I implement default methods in the interface? Let’s keep line lengths to 120 for Checkstyle and write the file.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_cITNFrie4gtlcH8QYBlwuCoN|fc_0593884d5898d8c70169f0dcd3c3d8819399b4df904bae218d", "name": "write", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.apache.tomcat.embed/tomcat-embed-websocket/9.0.83/src/test/java/org_apache_tomcat_embed/tomcat_embed_websocket/WsServerContainerTest.java", "content": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n */\npackage org_apache_tomcat_embed.tomcat_embed_websocket;\n\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\n\nimport java.io.InputStream;\nimport java.net.MalformedURLException;\nimport java.net.URL;\nimport java.util.Collection;\nimport java.util.Collections;\nimport java.util.Enumeration;\nimport java.util.EnumSet;\nimport java.util.EventListener;\nimport java.util.HashMap;\nimport java.util.Map;\nimport java.util.Set;\n\nimport javax.servlet.DispatcherType;\nimport javax.servlet.Filter;\nimport javax.servlet.FilterRegistration;\nimport javax.servlet.RequestDispatcher;\nimport javax.servlet.Servlet;\nimport javax.servlet.ServletContext;\nimport javax.servlet.ServletException;\nimport javax.servlet.ServletRegistration;\nimport javax.servlet.SessionCookieConfig;\nimport javax.servlet.SessionTrackingMode;\nimport javax.servlet.descriptor.JspConfigDescriptor;\nimport javax.websocket.EncodeException;\nimport javax.websocket.Encoder;\nimport javax.websocket.EndpointConfig;\nimport javax.websocket.OnOpen;\nimport javax.websocket.Session;\nimport javax.websocket.server.ServerEndpoint;\nimport javax.websocket.server.ServerEndpointConfig;\n\nimport org.apache.tomcat.websocket.server.Constants;\nimport org.apache.tomcat.websocket.server.WsMappingResult;\nimport org.apache.tomcat.websocket.server.WsSci;\nimport org.apache.tomcat.websocket.server.WsServerContainer;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\n\npublic class WsServerContainerTest {\n\n    @Test\n    public void startupRegistersAnnotatedEndpointWithCustomConfiguratorAndEncoder() throws Exception {\n        TestConfigurator.constructed = false;\n        TestEncoder.constructed = false;\n        TestServletContext servletContext = new TestServletContext();\n\n        new WsSci().onStartup(Collections.singleton(AnnotatedEndpoint.class), servletContext);\n\n        assertThat(TestConfigurator.constructed).isTrue();\n        assertThat(TestEncoder.constructed).isTrue();\n        Object container = servletContext.getAttribute(Constants.SERVER_CONTAINER_SERVLET_CONTEXT_ATTRIBUTE);\n        assertThat(container).isInstanceOf(WsServerContainer.class);\n\n        WsMappingResult mapping = ((WsServerContainer) container).findMapping(\"/ws/alpha\");\n        assertThat(mapping).isNotNull();\n        assertThat(mapping.getConfig().getEndpointClass()).isEqualTo(AnnotatedEndpoint.class);\n        assertThat(mapping.getPathParams()).containsEntry(\"name\", \"alpha\");\n    }\n\n    @ServerEndpoint(value = \"/ws/{name}\", configurator = TestConfigurator.class, encoders = TestEncoder.class)\n    public static class AnnotatedEndpoint {\n        @OnOpen\n        public void onOpen(Session session) {\n            assertThat(session).isNull();\n        }\n    }\n\n    public static class TestConfigurator extends ServerEndpointConfig.Configurator {\n        private static boolean constructed;\n\n        public TestConfigurator() {\n            constructed = true;\n        }\n    }\n\n    public static class TestEncoder implements Encoder.Text<String> {\n        private static boolean constructed;\n\n        public TestEncoder() {\n            constructed = true;\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        public void init(EndpointConfig config) {\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        public void destroy() {\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        public String encode(String object) throws EncodeException {\n            return object;\n        }\n    }\n\n    private static class TestServletContext implements ServletContext {\n        private final Map<String, Object> attributes = new HashMap<>();\n\n        @Override\n        public String getContextPath() {\n            return \"/test\";\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        public ServletContext getContext(String uripath) {\n            return null;\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        public int getMajorVersion() {\n            return 4;\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        public int getMinorVersion() {\n            return 0;\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        public int getEffectiveMajorVersion() {\n            return 4;\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        public int getEffectiveMinorVersion() {\n            return 0;\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        public String getMimeType(String file) {\n            return null;\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        public Set<String> getResourcePaths(String path) {\n            return Collections.emptySet();\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        public URL getResource(String path) throws MalformedURLException {\n            return null;\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        public InputStream getResourceAsStream(String path) {\n            return null;\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        public RequestDispatcher getRequestDispatcher(String path) {\n            return null;\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        public RequestDispatcher getNamedDispatcher(String name) {\n            return null;\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        public Servlet getServlet(String name) throws ServletException {\n            return null;\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        public Enumeration<Servlet> getServlets() {\n            return Collections.emptyEnumeration();\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        public Enumeration<String> getServletNames() {\n            return Collections.emptyEnumeration();\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        public void log(String msg) {\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        public void log(Exception exception, String msg) {\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        public void log(String message, Throwable throwable) {\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        public String getRealPath(String path) {\n            return null;\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        public String getServerInfo() {\n     